Since $\calS_x$ is convex, its tangent halfspace at $x$ is a supporting halfspace. 
Now fix $h>0$ and $u\in\mathbb{S}^{d-1}$.
If $x+hu\preccurlyeq x$, then by the second part of Lemma~\ref{lem:convex-supporting-halfspace}, we have $\langle n_x,u\rangle\le 0$.
This confirms that $\langle n_x,hu\rangle=\langle n_x,(x+hu)-x\rangle\le 0$, which is the desired conclusion.
\end{proof}

